                  "image": "{{step_1.data}}",
                  "prompt": "You are reading an academic transcript or diploma PDF issued by a non-Spanish university. Extract the following:\n1. country: the country where the issuing institution is located, written as the official Spanish-language country name in UPPERCASE (e.g. United States -> ESTADOS UNIDOS DE AMERICA, Germany -> ALEMANIA, United Kingdom -> REINO UNIDO). If it is not explicitly stated, infer it from the institution, language or address.\n2. grading_system: a short description of the grading scale used (e.g. 'US 4.0 GPA letter grades', 'German 1,0-5,0'), if identifiable; otherwise an empty string.\n3. grade_type: 'numerico' if grades are numbers, 'literal' if letters or words, 'mixto' if both.\n4. grades: every subject together with its grade. Copy the grade exactly as written, except normalise the decimal separator to a comma (3.7 -> 3,7) so it matches the reference dataset. Do not convert, round or translate the grade.",
                  "mode": "advanced",
                  "schema": {
                    "fields": {
                      "type": "object",
                      "properties": {
